race.comment: NATURAL ESSENCE (7) has a strong record here with three wins and two placings from seven starts. Was out of placings last time (21.08) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing fourth and beaten 3 lengths. Looks suited and should go close. FORNER'S FURY (1) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by a nose at this track in a handy 21.13 beating Paw Ricochet. One of main contenders. MISSION TO FLY (8) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when sixth at Muswellbrook over 431m behind Kiando Florence (25.44) in a Grade 5. Has ability and can measure up. ALL THE CASH (5) is one of the chances after collecting a minor prize last time.
